Can anyone help me how to get API tags in Kibana?

Below is my fluentd filter which I created now (but I unable to get any API tags under Kibana) :

filter-k8s-core.conf: |
    &lt;filter systemd.origin-master&gt;
      @type rewrite_tag_filter
      rewriterule1 _SYSTEMD_UNIT ^origin-master.service journal.system.kubernetes.master
      rewriterule2 _SYSTEMD_UNIT ^origin-node.service journal.system.kubernetes.node
    &lt;/filter&gt;
    &lt;filter journal.system.kubernetes.master&gt;
      @type record_transformer
      enable_ruby
      &lt;record&gt;
        k8s_api ${record['MESSAGE'].match(/GET \/api/)[0]}
      &lt;/record&gt;
    &lt;/filter&gt;

P.S. : I need want Kube API logs in journald

Thanks!

Hey, 

I'm working on having a fluentd filter to process kubernetes logs,

I edited the ConfigMap to add two files (in ingress):
      <@U1QLBGM7U> configs.d/user/filter-k8s-core-rewrite.conf
      <@U1QLBGM7U> configs.d/user/filter-k8s-core-data.conf

*First file is to rewrite the logs coming from services "origin-master" and "origin-node"*
filter-k8s-core-data.conf: |
    &lt;filter journal.system.kubernetes.master&gt;
      @type record_transformer
      enable_ruby
      &lt;record&gt;
        k8s_api ${record['MESSAGE'].match(/GET \/api/)[0]}
      &lt;/record&gt;
    &lt;/filter&gt;
*Second file is to tag all kubernetes namespaces:*
  filter-k8s-core-rewrite.conf: |
    &lt;match systemd.origin-master&gt;
      @type rewrite_tag_filter
      rewriterule1 _SYSTEMD_UNIT ^origin-master.service journal.system.kubernetes.master
      rewriterule2 _SYSTEMD_UNIT ^origin-node.service journal.system.kubernetes.node
    &lt;/match&gt;

But the problem is - what if there is no match for /.*GET/ ? What will the namespace name be?
and I'm not getting any logs under Kibana with API tags?

Can anyone help me out here?

Anyone knows how to add this to current config (in fluentd filter)?

&lt;record&gt;
     unused ${record['MESSAGE'].match(/.*GET\s\/api.*namespaces\/(\w*)\//) do |md| record['kubernetes']=Hash.new; record['kubernetes']['namespace_name']=md[1] end}
   &lt;/record&gt;
   remove_keys unused

I tested the expression in fluentular : <https://fluentular.herokuapp.com/>, however, I'm not sure if I'm doing it right.
The intention is that in a line that comes from journald like this:
ago 21 18:19:12 viaq.logging.test origin-master[1194]: I0821 18:19:12.249226    1194 panics.go:76] GET /api/v1/namespaces/logging/endpoints/logging-kibana: (10.89128ms) 200 [[openshift/v1.5.2+43a9be4 (linux/amd64) kubernetes/43a9be4 system:serviceaccount:openshift-infra:endpoint-controller] 192.168.122.5:47476 &lt;http://192.168.122.5:47476&gt;]

